	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>except that the AWH leggings give +25AGI also..DOH!<br>which is about +5AC gives you +30AC total plus and extra +5Sta<br><br>Let me clue you in on reality thats not clouded by pagan AC m0nkeyB0yE worship....<br><br>Unless that extra 16AC is going to put you over your next 100AC barrier (1000/1100/1200etc)then the extra 16AC is totally meaningless esp to a NON plate class...Monks like Beastlords are an AVOIDANCE class....+25 AGI will do way more for you than that +16AC...<br><br>Plus you get an extra 20HPs.....<br><br>Even if as a Monk you can get your AC up to 1400AC (which basically means you just F*cked yourself out of something like AGI/Sta etc to get that high a AC) then your still NOT going to mitigate damage as well as a Warrior with just 1000AC.....your better off with 1200AC and 250+AGI than 1400AC with 100AGI.....<br><br>and a Beastlord could use any of those legs you listed every bit as much as a Monk, and if they dont have better (which they wont cuz these are about as good as it gets for a beast)then they have just as much right to have a chance at them...<br>In the 'UBER guild&quot; as you put it, Monks are dime a dozen...a good high lvl 62+ Beastlord isnt..(I was in TOV a couple weeks ago was 129 in zone..I was the ONLY Beastlord).....and technically a Beast has just as much if not MORE to offer a raiding party than any Monk.<br>also as a general rule a high lvl Beastlord will be doing as much if not more melee as a Monk and IF they happen to be one of the slowers or &quot;PREslowers&quot; &amp; Debuffers then will without a doubt draw more aggro than a Monk...<br>A Monk can FD, Beast cant....I sometimes PREslow standing right next to the Warrior so there is no ping pong and no aggro onto the Ench or Shaman when they use thier better slow &amp; Debuff....<br>So as a Beast we will usually take MORE hits than the average Monk...Ive had just my Reposte keep aggro for a few secs.....<br>any guild that would just automatically hand these to a Monk is a clueless guild....<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
