	   <a name=104204194815635></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104204194815635><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6322&mid=104204194815635>awarding by classism</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6322&mid=104204194815635#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97334><span id= >Gilraven</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 8th 11:33 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Couple of things: First, there's a great way to tell whether an item is MEANT for a certain class. Just look at the class restrictions on the item. If your class is listed, it was meant for you. No one can tell anyone else what loot is &quot;correct&quot; for their character. Someone mentioned, for instance, that rangers should look at Onyx Chain legs instead. Well, for myself and as a ranger, HP is all-important. In a raid environment AC is nice, but completely secondary. So, that being said, this item is vastly superior IMHO. <br><br>Second, in response to the analysis that monks should get this item because you can't pull without them...well, bear in mind that I am saying this as a representative of a nearly useless raid class, but monks are not CRITICAL to raid success...we often pull with a shadowknight. I'm not saying you monks aren't useful, but don't go getting all uppity and pretending that you should be given special consideration because the world revolves around you. ;)<br>&nbsp;<br>Gilraven Silverthorne<br>60th Ranger of Eternal Retribution<br>Tunare Server</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
