	   <tr><td colspan=2>Serberus, you have NO idea how to play a Shaman, for one.&nbsp;&nbsp;Read the Shaman's Crucible.  The vast majority of Shaman who have thought about gear, fought over gear, discussed gear with each other, have come to the conclusion that<br><br>   hp regen &gt; hp/STA &gt; AC &gt; mana &gt; WIS<br><br>Where resists fall into this scheme is very complex, but those items have a very clear hierarchy.  Why?  Because it's not the SIZE of your mana pool that counts, but how fast you can REFILL it.  With Cannibalization, HP == MANA.  Given a higher AC, you'll keep more HP and therefore have more mana.<br><br>For a level 60+ Shaman with Torpor and possibly the Cann 5 AA skill, mana is just Not An Issue.  One Cann 5 and your mana bar is full.  A couple of 250 mana Torpors later and your health bars is full, too.  WIS becomes simply irrelevant.<br><br>So yeah, these legs are pretty awesome for Shaman and using my guild's modified DKP system I would happily roll against monks for them.  It's cases like this that point systems were made for, so folks who have never played a class can't dictate which loot items that class gets.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Twoflower Tourist<br>61 Oracle...<br>... and levelling slowly<br>Union of Power - Rodcet Nife</td></tr>
